<article>
    <h1>CHRIST&#xAD;MAS CON&#xAD;CERTS COME TO&#xAD;GETHER</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE WEEKEND</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Es­planade’s month-long col­lab­o­ra­tive con­cert se­ries Come To­gether in­cludes Christ­mas-themed con­certs.</p>
    <p>Cul­tural Medal­lion re­cip­i­ent Louis So­liano (be­low), one of the home-grown jazz scene’s most es­tab­lished mu­si­cians, will per­form Christ­mas clas­sics such as</p>
    <p>The Christ­mas Song,</p>
    <p>My Grown Up</p>
    <p>Christ­mas List and</p>
    <p>Sleigh Ride.</p>
    <p>Ac­com­pa­nied by mu­si­cians such as singer Re­becca</p>
    <p>Al­wani and vi­olin­ist</p>
    <p>Karen de</p>
    <p>Silva, his gigs will take place live at the Es­planade Con­course and on­line at the arts cen­tre’s web­site at 6.45pm and 8.30pm to­day.</p>
    <p>Also to­day, the Lyre­birds, a group com­pris­ing singers and the­atre prac­ti­tion­ers such as Inch Chua, Cren­shaw Yeo and Di­nesh Balasingam, will sing Broad­way Christ­mas num­bers at the Es­planade Out­door The­atre at 7.30pm and 9pm. WHERE Var­i­ous venues at Es­planade, 1 Es­planade Drive; on­line at bit.ly/34FuTC1</p>
    <p>MRT Es­planade</p>
    <p>WHEN Un­til Thurs­day, var­i­ous times</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION Free</p>
    <p>INFO For line-up and de­tails, go to bit.ly/34FuTC1</p>

